def greet(name: str) -> str:
    """
    Returns a greeting message for a given name.
    """
    return f"Hello, {name}! Welcome to this GitHub project."

if __name__ == "__main__":
    print(greet("Developer"))
# Simple Greeting Project

This is a simple Python project designed as an example for publishing on GitHub.  
It includes a basic function that returns a greeting message.

